comment: Smart (BOS) makes contact with Irving's (CLE) jersey but does not affect his SQBR.
Smart (BOS) makes marginal contact with Smith (CLE) that does not affect his SQBR.
Olynyk (BOS) legally contests Love's (CLE) jump shot attempt. Any "high-five" contact after the release is considered incidental.
Horford (BOS) sets the screen on Smith (CLE) and gives him room to avoid the contact.
[Observable in enhanced video] Bradley (BOS) lifts his pivot foot at the start of his dribble.
After communicating with the Replay Center, the ruling on the floor of a 3pt field goal at the 3:10 mark is confirmed.
Smith (CLE) jumps from point A to point B into the body of Smart (BOS) and the contact affects his jump shot attempt.
Smart (BOS) allows Irving (CLE) to land following the jump shot attempt.
Thompson (CLE) makes marginal contact with Horford (BOS) that does not affect his SQBR and shot attempt.
Horford (BOS) makes incidental contact with Thompson (CLE) on the shot attempt.
Crowder (BOS) makes marginal contact with James (CLE) that does not affect his SQBR.
Smart (BOS) continues moving into Irving (CLE) and affects his ability to defend the play.
Jerebko's (BOS) foot is touching the three-point arc and the shot is correctly ruled a 2pt field goal on the floor.
Crowder (BOS) makes marginal contact with Love (CLE) off ball.
Horford (BOS) makes marginal contact with James (CLE) that does not affect his SQBR.
